  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed across blood viscosity, inlet flow boundary conditions, and rotational speed tolerances using a Monte Carlo propagation approach; a screening sensitivity study was conducted to rank input contributions to the relative hemolysis index, confirming viscosity and flow rate as leading contributors. UQ results are summarized in the attached computational report.",
